Key to beating a necromancer:<br>
1) Have annull/nullify magic memorized and have your first two buff spots open.  Most of the necromancer dots are magic based but are unresistable.  The heat blood, darkness, BoD/Vexing lines can be dispelled.  If the necro casts BoD or Vexing, make sure you dispell it off them as well.  Golem wands are extremely helpful.<br>
<br>
2) Know where your pet is at all times.  If the necromancer starts fearing your pet, a) interrupt it with your level 8 nuke, OR b) target your pet and annull it right away.<br>
<br>
3) If the necromancer is busy with your pet, he is not busy with you.. Make use of this.<br>
<br>
4) Magician pets &gt; Necromancer pets.  If the necro does not know how to PvP, he will let the two pets fight.  Buy your time by interrupting his spells.<br>
<br>
5) If the necromancer has a pet of his own, use your sow potion or jboots to run around until your pet is no longer feared and is occupied with the necro pet or the necromancer himself.  You will never channell through the necro pet spam.  So make sure you use the fact that necros don't have expedience.<br>
<br>
6) Deflux is nasty and most likely will be the spell a necromancer is using against you.  Do not stand in range for it, otherwise you will not survive.  Go out of it's range, cast Scars or Char while he is running.  If he is running close to you, run out of deflux range again.<br>
<br>
7) Remember, against a necromancer, time is your best friend.  With time, the necromancer's Fear spell on your pet will wear off. <p>"So you think your kung-fu's pretty good, huh? I want to fight your brother... him.. against.. me.. LET'S KUNG-FOO!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(9/1/01 4:41:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage VS Necro duel</span><hr size=1> I had the opportunity to go toe to toe against a level 49 necro (when I was 49). I had my 49 earth pet, 44 pets of all sorts. He had a level 44 necro pet, no 49 pet. 5 battles, he won all of the, but I learned a few things.<br>
<br>
1) Don't forget how to armor your pet. Boost his MR by 15 by giving him *3* Daggers of Symbols. (One is a range slot, hopefully it's equipped). Can also give him 2 Coldstones (There's an AC component on there), such as it's help would be used.<br>
<br>
2) Have Shock of Swords memmed (whichever is the fast cast, low level shock spell). Use it often to attempt to disrupt him.<br>
<br>
3) Don't forget your Staff of Cancel Magic <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I did, and I figure it might've actually been usefull to me.<br>
<br>
4) I went in with a few different kinds of pets. Earth, and Air (44). I wager the low level of the air pet caused it to suffer in resists, it did seem to me that I did best with my air pet. For some reason, the air pet broke the fear far earlier than the earth pet did.<br>
<br>
5) Layer your self buffs such that your MR shielding is LAST, preceeded by the Ele Armor, Phatom Armor, and as many other self-buffs as you can get (see invis, levi, etc). This will aid in you resisting his spells. Here, +MR gear doesn't hurt at all.<br>
<br>
6) Have a DD Vs Summoned spell memmed, as fast a cast as you think you can handle. I did manage to lay waste to one necro pet while it was attacking me using a DS on myself + the DD Vs Summoned line. Unfortunately, by that time, I had been debuffed, and owned.<br>
<br>
Had I had more MR gear, I know at least one fight would've gone better for me. I got chewed on ONLY because my last shielding spell (Arch Shield) got dispelled, and my MR dropped too low. I had the Necro well hampered and near dead.<br>
<br>
I have, as of yet, not won against a Necro, but then, I'm still hunting for +MR gear to boost my chances next time I try. Feel free to take my lessons or not, they're simple tactics that I tried that SEEM to have done fairly well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utrezark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trezark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(1/24/02 3:59:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://shadowblazer.armageddongames.com/images/Trezark/ezhmage.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage VS Necro duel</span><hr size=1> I came in here intending to find a good thread regarding the Mage vs. Necro duel and found, to my surprise, a post referencing me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I was the 45 mage Solistus was talking about that got beat down by my level 45 guild leader time and time again.  Feared Pet + Skelly on me + Lifetaps = mean.<br>
<br>
I'm hoping to make a go of it again though...  I'm now level 52 and the necro in question is 54.  Hopefully the level difference won't be that big of an issue if I play my cards right.  My biggest problem though is that my resistances aren't too hot (probably need to work on that) but here's something I was considering:  Would the level 52 Fire Pet be a good choice in this situation?  My plan is to use Ensnaring Roots (via a stockpile of Crystalline Silk Nets I got from CC) on his pet as soon as the battle starts, and send the fire pet after him.  What I'm <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> HOPING</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is that the fire pet coupled with my DD will interrupt him enough to keep him from getting fear on my pet and keep him from being able to put too much hurt on me.<br>
<br>
So the real question here is, will a Vocerate Fire be able to interrupt a 54 Necromancer often enough to make a difference?   <p><BR><CENTER><hr size=1 WIDTH=75%>
<font face=arial size=-2>[52 Elementalist] <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46277">Trezark S`Dious</A> (Dark Elf) &lt;<A HREF="http://www.blackreignguild.freeservers.com/">Black Reign</A>&gt; SERVER: Vazaelle<BR><b>Last Recorded Ding:</b> [Fri Jan 18 10:06:46 2002] You have gained a level! Welcome to level 52!<br><i>"You could no more evade my wrath than you could your own shadow..."</i></FONT></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrumples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grumples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#333333>(2/2/02 2:14:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage VS Necro duel</span><hr size=1> You should run some tests with the firepet.  I hear a lot of mixed reviews.  Some people say it's the best thing since sliced bread when it comes to PvP.  Others say how they like to solo Sirens with their firepet because they resist 95% of the pet's spells when it gets charmed.<br>
<br>
Fighting necros is a matter of time and space.<br>
The longer you live the harder it gets on the necro, and you need space to run around and avoid getting cast on.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't suggest trying to interrupt him too much.  At this level, Shock of Blades really doesn't interrupt worth poop unless you're fighting someone in water.  He'll just deflux you death even with the pet beating on him.<br>
<br>
Basically try to stay out of range, make sure your pet beats his pet as fast as possible and run him OOM from casting Fear spells.  If you want to be clever you can start nullifying your pet when you see him start doing a fear effect.  Bring Crystallized Pumice and your dispells are free.<br>
<br>
The art of fighting with a mage is the art of running away.<br>
