alive 205 HP at a time.  When you're 150-200 feet away, stop and cast Scars at him.  If your pet is feared and his is backed off, his pet will jump you shortly.  It will also beat itsself to death on your DS in seconds, don't worry about it.  At this point you have already won the fight...He has 300 damage streaking towards him, and you're out of his spell range.  Stand your ground until you see him stop to cast, then you should be moving again.  The idea behind this method is that you don't ever get anything cast on you.  Your pet is your time buffer, the necro can't do jack until he takes care of your pet because his pet is already dead by the time he blinks.<br>
<br>
Why do you have Scintillation up?  Just in case that pet bashes you, or the necro lands a snare and happens to get in range...Scint is a 1 foot knockback, did you know that?  Interrupts handily at times, 3 seconds, 450 damage or so in PVP.  <br>
<br>
<br>
See how it works...after I came up with this (fairly obvious) technique, I never lost to a necro again.<br>
